caption: Fantastic food, very friendly employees, consistently  awesome ambience. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is very good. 5 stars.

Showed up in 15 minutes as they said, and it wasn’t kept in a warmer and was pretty much inedible.. crust was chewy and wet, couldn’t find the cheese and very little bland tomato sauce, tasted like from a can...many better places to get pizza around here and won’t  make this mistake again! Seeing the fire oven is wicked cool since the dining room didn't get any heat from the oven. Staff is wicked friendly and always there when you need them. We all enjoyed our meals here, and the nutella pizza dessert is yummy! (It's a little loud in there but that was the only drawback).

Ordered beer from the menu, they were out. Ordered second beer, they no longer carried it. Ordered Bud, again, from the menu, no longer carried. Ordered a Mic, the brought me Mic lite. Plus, I never received my pizza. Oh well.

Highly recommend! Even for a busy Saturday night, the service was fast and excellent. We were in and out in 1.5 hours - eating 3 courses. The food and drinks were absolutely incredible. Calamari was well cooked and fresh, lasagna and pizza were just as good as what we've had over in Italy, and the Zeppelos dessert were delicious (think donuts with nutella and ricotta for dipping). What a great experience yet again at Charcoal Guido's. Amazing pizza, apps, salads, and dessert. Not to mention the best espresso martini in town and top notch service. We have only had Mario is our sever and we wouldn't have it any other way. He is kind, welcoming, and attentive. He remembered who we were and what our order was, even after our first experience. In addition- after we had ordered something that wasn't exactly what we had expected (not bad, just not exactly what we had in mind), we communicated it to him and he was so gracious and sweet about it. We will continue to go back and ask for Mario as our server. Thank you for another lovely night!

Always excellent!  We hold a yearly luncheon at Charcoal Guido's and everyone there is so helpful and professional.  The food is superior and the drinks and service are like none other.  We love it there!

Disclaimer:  I know and work with the owner of this restaurant.  I only recently learned about Charcoal Guido's, after meeting and getting to know the management of this establishment.  My first experience with the food here was at a catered event, and I immediately took a liking the the meatballs.  After trying a nice variety of their dishes, I feel confident saying that this is some of the best Italian food I have ever had, and also some of the most unique.  The specials are inspired dishes that the staff have come up with, and they really hit it out of the park with the sweet and spicy calamari.  Another noteworthy dish is the Nutella pizza, which to me, is synonymous with Charcoal Guido's.  Do yourself a favor and don't pass this place by like I did for years.   On top of all the great food, the service is truly outstanding, and you can tell right away that the staff enjoy working here.  Thank you for all the amazing nights out I have had here!
Great service, especially at the bar. Food was good, but I've had better pizza. Highly reccomend their gnocci and pasta dishes. Great ambiance, higher end of the price spectrum, good for date night!

Always a great meal here with a fantastic, attentive staff! This time I had Lasagna Bolognese. It wasn't a piece, it was a slab! And the Nutella Pizza lives up to the hype! This place is worth the drive from anywhere!
Drinks are amazing and food as well. My wife and I had a great time.

It clearly says the lunch pizzas were served starting at 1130. The interesting thing is that they only have one server. She was great but it can't be expected to have prompt service if she is the only one servicing 30 people. It just isn't fair or right.

This place is amazing. The best service I've received in 20+ years, maybe ever. My experience was so exceptional it motivated me to write this my first review ever. My date and I were treated like we were personal friends on the owner. Nick was my server and when he found out it was our first time there, he made it a point to make us feel welcomed. I was blown away when one of the owners stopped by and chatted with us to see if everything was perfect. It was more than perfect, it was exceptional!  Thank you for the hospitality and the amazing food. By the way the pizza with the arugula, figs, Gorgonzola cheese, caramelized onion. was amazing. I don't even like arugula, but damn it was good. I'm definitely going to order it again. Thank you.

If you visit, make sure you try their signature Nutella pizza. This dessert, large enough for 3 or 4 to share, is spectacular; my mouth is watering just thinking about it. Do make reservations, especially on the weekends, as it gets busy. This is one of the better places to eat or enjoy a drink on Moody street.

Not really sure what to say about this place to be honest. The Food isn't terrible, its actually pretty decent...but ridiculously overpriced for portion sizes.  We're talking Posto (the best italian that I've had in Boston) prices, for food that isn't even close to Posto's food quality.  Portions are STINGY      (you get a half teaspoon of olive oil to use as dipping sauce....for 4 people!)  Tables are crammed literally inches away from each other to pack in as many paying customers as possible...but so tightly packed that it feels like your sitting on top of the people next to you. The problem could easily be alleviated by removing 1 table, but if they're giving you a half a teaspoon of olive oil, instead of giving you a bottle to pour your own, that tells you everything you need to know about where the owner's priorities are. That said, the waitstaff is always very courteous and attentive, and extremely pleasant.  It's a shame, because with lower prices, more generous portions and 1 less table to give you some breathing room, this could be a decent little place to eat.  Edit: So i just went back to this place a few weeks ago, and with my dinner, I ordered a side of plain french fries.  When the bill came at the end of the meal, I realized that they charge me $8 .....FOR A SIDE OF FRENCH FRIES!!!!   I gave this place one more shot, and learned my lesson.  Unless you enjoy paying $8 for french fries, sitting on top of the people eating next to you, and having to pay for coffee refills, skip this place.  A ton of restaurants on Moody St. that will treat you much better as a patron.

Everything here is handmade and delicious, the drinks are great. My personal favorite is the gnocchi but every time my boyfriend and I go, we're always incredibly impressed by the food, service, and atmosphere

First of all it's very popular so reservations are a must! Next the food is to die for.  Last time I was there I tried the Calamari and it was very very good.  The Calamari wasn't buried in batter; in fact it was very light and very tasty, one of the best I've ever had! Next are the handmade wood fired pizza's; my favorites are the FIGS AND GORGONZOLA and the WHITE DEVIL.  Oh and if you can get the table right in front of the brick oven then you can watch your pizzas being made. Every time I go we've finished with the NUTELLA PIZZA with strawberries, it just melts in your mouth. I can't wait to go back.
Great food; great environment.  Must go if you like Italian.

I've been here many times and I always love it. When you walk in it seems really noisy - and I guess it is - and it seems like a lot of people crammed together in one place - and I guess it is. But, as soon as you sit down, it no longer seems noisy, but lively, and it no longer seems crammed-in, but familiar. People just always seem to be in a good mood when they're there. You are sitting close (like in a restaurant you might find in France or Italy) and every single time, we end up having really nice conversations with the folks at the next table. Last night, we sang happy birthday to the little girl at the table to my right, and we talked about travel and dining with the Irish guy to my left. It seems like barriers are taken down and people are just there for a nice time with other people who want to have a nice time. It's a bit loud for sure, but not in the least boisterous - just the sound of happy people.  I lived in Italy for four years. I make my own pasta, my own sauces, my own risotto - and I'm pretty pleased that they are really authentic to what I grew to love in Italy. I don't order pasta in restaurants usually because, more often than not, I make better at home. This place, though. They have the best bolognese meat sauce I've had on this side of the Atlantic. They make their pasta in-house. The pizzas are fired in a brick oven and they are the real thing - like what one would get in Rome, not Waltham.  When you sit down you get fresh pizza bianca slivers and extra virgin olive oil for dipping. And they replenish it when you're done.  They do not skimp on portions. The salads are huge. Usually when a wait-person says the salads are big, what I get is something have the size of what I eat at home as part of my meal. But these are really big. We shared the roasted beet and goat cheese salad. Delicious.  I ordered the tagliatelle bolognese and my husband had the fig and arugula pizza. The pizza has enough arugula on it to make another salad. You can certainly get a pizza with more traditional toppings, but you can also get some combinations you've maybe never tried before. But they are all really good. The pizza is thin crust and has the characteristic of being crunchy and chewy at the same time.  We had cannoli for desert - not that I had much room, but I had to try one. Totally authentic and delicious.  I like sitting on the side of the table that faces the wall because there are enormous photographs of Italy - and they bring me down memory lane from when I lived there.  Their wine list isn't extensive, but they have a short list of nice wines. Three or four of them are quite expensive - most of them are very moderately priced. We had a wonderful Montepulciano for $30. It was so good I want to see if I can hunt it down to have at home.  Prices are very reasonable for food and drink. Staff are incredibly friendly. Service is prompt. There's no sense of ever being rushed.  If you are looking for a quiet, romantic dinner - Charcoal Guido's is not for you. If you are the type that doesn't like dining in close quarters - then this isn't for you. If you like REAL Italian food (not American Italian), and if you don't mind meeting some people while you sip your wine waiting for your meal, and if you like a place where everyone always seems to be in a good mood - then check this place out.  If this description sounds like a fun time to you, and you decide to check it out, Charcoal Guido's will become one of your favorite go-to's.
Amazing food, amazing ambiance, and amazing employees. Owner is the nicest guy you’ll ever meet. Highly recommend! Nutella pizza is unreal!

We did 80% of the work and he did not ask us how much work would be done at the beginning, we did the work by the hour ... when I sent the bill dise that it was very expensive that it would not pay me this amount ... spend a few weeks sent me a and said he would hire another company to finish the job and that he would not pay me the remainder of nearly $ 1,800.
